wikilib.d/PmWiki.BasicEditing,675
text=The pages on this site are [[WikiWikiWeb]] pages, which means that pages can be created and edited by multiple authors. To edit a page, click the '''Edit Page''' link that exists somewhere on the page (usually in the header or footer). Some pages may be [[password(s)]]-protected, depending on how others have configured the security on the system, but many WikiWikiWeb systems allow open editing of all pages.²²The rules for basic page editing are fairly simple--start each line without spaces and put a blank line between paragraphs. You can produce well-laid out pages by learning just '''five rules'''. ²# to make a list (like this one), start each line with 9,335

